I subset the DILIConcern data by those drugs that have the same label in the columns DILIConcern and vDILIConcern.

drank.sel$DILIConcern[drank.sel$DILIConcern == "No-DILI-concern"] <- "No-DILI-Concern" # Correct the 4 entries with lowercase concern
# We remove the first letter from vDILIConcern entries (except Ambiguous)
drank.sel$vDILIConcern[drank.sel$vDILIConcern != "Ambiguous DILI-concern"] <- sub('.', '', drank.sel$vDILIConcern[drank.sel$vDILIConcern != "Ambiguous DILI-concern"])

no_concern_drugs <- dilirank_df$pert_iname[dilirank_df$DILIConcern == "No-DILI-Concern"]

Compare the expression of each gene across samples of Most-DILI-Concern vs.Â No-DILI-Concern in PHH cell line, 10 ÂµM and 24 h

For each gene, we will check the difference of expression between Most-DILI-Concern drugs and No-DILI-Concern drugs using a Wilcoxon rank-sum test (or Mann-Whitney U test) (More info).

# Create new dataframe to store the results
cols <- c("gene_id", "landmark", "statistic", "p.value")
wilcox_df <- data.frame(matrix(ncol = length(cols), nrow=0))
colnames(wilcox_df) <- cols

# Calculate the wilcoxon for each gene and store the results
#output_table <- "/home/quim/PHD/Projects/camda/results/gene_test_phh_10_24.tsv"
output_table <- "/home/quim/PHD/Projects/camda/results/gene_test_landmark_phh_10_24_mixlessmost.tsv"
if(!file.exists(output_table)){
  #for (gene_id in gct_most_phh_10_24@rid) {
  for (gene_id in landmark_genes) {
    most_expr <- gct_most_phh_10_24@mat[gct_most_phh_10_24@rid == gene_id]
    no_expr <- gct_no_phh_10_24@mat[gct_no_phh_10_24@rid == gene_id]
    res <- wilcox.test(most_expr, no_expr, alternative = "two.sided", paired = FALSE)
    landmark <- gene_id %in% landmark_genes
    wilcox_df[nrow(wilcox_df)+1,] <- c(gene_id, landmark, res$statistic, res$p.value)
  }
  wilcox_df$p.value <- as.numeric(wilcox_df$p.value)
  wilcox_df$p.adjust <- p.adjust(wilcox_df$p.value, "BH")
  write.table(wilcox_df, file = output_table,row.names=FALSE, na="-",col.names=TRUE, sep="\t")
}else{
  wilcox_df = read.csv(output_table, header = TRUE, sep = "\t")
}
head(wilcox_df)

We will make a heatmap to plot the expression of the genes for each drug.

# Define the genes found
all_wilcox_gene_ids <- unique(wilcox_df$gene_id[wilcox_df$p.value<0.01])
all_wilcox_gene_ids_05 <- unique(wilcox_df$gene_id[wilcox_df$p.value<0.05])
landmark_wilcox_gene_ids <- unique(wilcox_df$gene_id[wilcox_df$p.value<0.01 & wilcox_df$landmark==TRUE])
landmark_wilcox_gene_ids_05 <- unique(wilcox_df$gene_id[wilcox_df$p.value<0.05 & wilcox_df$landmark==TRUE])

# Get a vector of gene symbols ordered equal to the vector of gene IDs
genes_selected <- landmark_wilcox_gene_ids_05
genes_df <- data.frame(1:length(genes_selected), genes_selected)
colnames(genes_df)<- c("id", "pr_gene_id")
genes_df <- merge(genes_df, gene_info_df[,c("pr_gene_id", "pr_gene_symbol")], by="pr_gene_id")
genes_df <- genes_df[order(genes_df$id), ]
genes_df$id <- NULL

# Create new dataframe to store the matrix
cols <- c(most_concern_drugs, no_concern_drugs)
rows <- genes_df$pr_gene_symbol
heat_df <- data.frame(matrix(ncol = length(cols), nrow=length(rows)))
colnames(heat_df) <- cols
rownames(heat_df) <- rows
gene_ids <- genes_df$pr_gene_id

# Introduce the data in the matrix
for (drug in most_concern_drugs){
  id_drug <- which(gct_most_phh_10_24@cdesc$pert_iname == drug)
  id_genes <- which(gct_most_phh_10_24@rid %in% gene_ids)
  gct_drug <- subset.gct(gct_most_phh_10_24, cid=id_drug, rid=id_genes)
  #means<- rowMeans(gct_drug@mat)
  medians <- apply(gct_drug@mat, 1, median) 
  heat_df[drug] <- medians
}
for (drug in no_concern_drugs){
  id_drug <- which(gct_no_phh_10_24@cdesc$pert_iname == drug)
  id_genes <- which(gct_no_phh_10_24@rid %in% gene_ids)
  gct_drug <- subset.gct(gct_no_phh_10_24, cid=id_drug, rid=id_genes)
  #means<- rowMeans(gct_drug@mat)
  medians <- apply(gct_drug@mat, 1, median) 
  heat_df[drug] <- medians
}
# Save the table
output_table <- "/home/quim/PHD/Projects/camda/results/gene_test_heatmap_data_phh_10_24_mixlessmost.tsv"

Perform the same analysis removing the outliers daunorubicin and vorinostat

# Remove daunorubicin and vorinostat from no_concern_drugs
outliers = c('daunorubicin', 'vorinostat')
no_concern_drugs_noout <- no_concern_drugs[!no_concern_drugs %in% outliers]
id_no_phh_10_24_noout <- which(!gct_no_phh_10_24@cdesc$pert_iname %in% outliers)
gct_no_phh_10_24_noout <- subset.gct(gct_no_phh_10_24, cid=id_no_phh_10_24_noout)

# Create new dataframe to store the results
cols <- c("gene_id", "landmark", "statistic", "p.value")
wilcox_noout_df <- data.frame(matrix(ncol = length(cols), nrow=0))
colnames(wilcox_noout_df) <- cols

# Calculate the wilcoxon for each gene and store the results
#output_table <- "/home/quim/PHD/Projects/camda/results/gene_test_phh_10_24_noout.tsv"
output_table <- "/home/quim/PHD/Projects/camda/results/gene_test_landmark_phh_10_24_noout_mixlessmost.tsv"
if(!file.exists(output_table)){
  #for (gene_id in gct_most_phh_10_24@rid) {
  for (gene_id in landmark_genes) {
    most_expr <- gct_most_phh_10_24@mat[gct_most_phh_10_24@rid == gene_id]
    no_expr <- gct_no_phh_10_24_noout@mat[gct_no_phh_10_24_noout@rid == gene_id]
    res <- wilcox.test(most_expr, no_expr, alternative = "two.sided", paired = FALSE)
    landmark <- gene_id %in% landmark_genes
    wilcox_noout_df[nrow(wilcox_noout_df)+1,] <- c(gene_id, landmark, res$statistic, res$p.value)
  }
  wilcox_noout_df$p.value <- as.numeric(wilcox_noout_df$p.value)
  wilcox_noout_df$p.adjust <- p.adjust(wilcox_noout_df$p.value, "BH")
  write.table(wilcox_noout_df, file = output_table,row.names=FALSE, na="-",col.names=TRUE, sep="\t")
}else{
  wilcox_noout_df = read.csv(output_table, header = TRUE, sep = "\t")
